Release-01 Changes:
-------------------
1). Add webservice to find max number

Techologies:
------------
Maven, Jetty, Maven-Jetty plugin, angularjs, restful webservices, angular-js ajax and json.

Accessing posts using angularjs:-

http://localhost:8082/angularjs-app   - Routing is default to post.html url
http://localhost:8082/angularjs-app/#/post

Accessing posts through webservice:
http://localhost:8082/angularjs-app/rs/post?pageNumber=1

Accessing comments through webservice:
http://localhost:8082/angularjs-app/rs/post/comment?postId=1


Access email validator:
http://localhost:8082/angularjs-app/#/email

access number sum webservice:
http://localhost:8082/angularjs-app/rs/sum?number=3303


NOTE:
-----
1). hostname, port number and context-root will change according to the
   deployment. Please change accordingly.
   http://{hostname:port}/{your-contextroot}/rs/sum?number=3303


2). Maven is used in this project to build and test, for testing jetty server plugin 
    is configured in pom.xml.
    jetty server is configured on port 8082 for http and 8083 for stoping jetty
 
2.1). Copy the project.
2.2). mvn clean install -U (creates the war file in target folder).
2.3). mvn jetty:run (runs the jetty and deploys the war file in the target folder).
2.4). mvn jetty:stop (stops jetty, open another commnad prompt and type this command).

Deployment in tomcat:
--------------------
3) Once you compiled and build using maven, copy the war file from target folder
   3.1)drop the war in the tomcat/webapps folder
   3.2)check server.xml for port which is running
    <Connector port="9090" protocol="HTTP/1.1"
               connectionTimeout="20000"
               redirectPort="8443" />
   3.3)Check context-root 
